Dr. and Mrs. Terence J. McGrath of Chappaqua, N.Y., have announced the engagement of their daughter, Kathleen Anne McGrath, to Brian D. Dunn, son of Mr. and Mrs. J. Norton Dunn of White Plains.

A June wedding is planned.

Miss McGrath, who expects to receive a master's degree from the Columbia University Graduate School of Business in May, graduated from the Georgetown University College of Arts and Sciences, having studied economics during the junior year at the University of Brussels. Her father is a dentist in Pleasantville, N.Y. Her mother, Anne R. McGrath, is a travel agent with McGregor Travel Inc. in Greenwich, Conn.

The future bride is a granddaughter of Christopher C. McGrath, retired Surrogate of Bronx County and a Democratic Representative in Washington from 1948 to 1952.

Mr. Dunn, a consultant in the New York office of Towers, Perrin, Forster & Crosby, a human resources and management concern, received B.S. and M.B.A. degrees from Cornell University. His father is president of J. Norton Dunn Associates, a management consulting firm in White Plains. His mother, Fiora P. Dunn, is a travel agent with Haigh-Donovan Travel Inc. in Port Chester, N.Y.